-----------------------------------------------------
CONTROL-FLOW and DATA-FLOW for Java 1.4 and Java 5.
These modules are part of the JastAdd project (http://www.jastadd.org).
The source code copyright is held by Emma Söderberg, emma@cs.lth.se, and is covered by the BSD license.

For more information, see the following paper:
Emma Nilsson-Nyman, Görel Hedin, Eva Magnusson, Torbjörn Ekman: Declarative Intraprocedural Flow Analysis of Java Source Code. Electr. Notes Theor. Comput. Sci. 238(5): 155-171 (2009). http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.entcs.2009.09.046
-----------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
The modules depend on the JastAddJ frontends for Java1.4 and Java1.5, which should be located in the following sibling directories (or adapt the build.xml file):
  ../Java1.4Frontend
  ../Java1.5Frontend
All tools needed (jastadd2, jflex, beaver, etc.) are included in Java1.4Frontend. You only need to have javac and Apache Ant installed in order to continue.
-----------------------------------------------------
BUILD
Build is done by an ant build.xml file.

- Ordinary build (generate and compile):
    > ant

- Remove all generated files and class files
    > ant clean
----------------------------------------------------
RUN
An example main program JavaDeadAssignCheckerExpr.java is included that parses Java source code, and outputs information about dead assignments.

Usage: java JavaDeadAssignCheckerExpr <options> <source files>
  -verbose                  Output messages about what the compiler is doing
  -classpath <path>         Specify where to find user class files
  -sourcepath <path>        Specify where to find input source files
  -bootclasspath <path>     Override location of bootstrap class files
  -extdirs <dirs>           Override location of installed extensions
  -d <directory>            Specify where to place generated class files
  -help                     Print a synopsis of standard options
  -version                  Print version information
